      • fromItemStack

        public static NBTCompound fromItemStack(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item)
                                 throws NMSException
        Returns the NBT tag for the specified item. The tag is read-write, and any modification applied to it will also be applied to the item's NBT tag.
        Parameters:
        item - The item to get the tag from.
        Returns:
        the NBT tag for the specified item.
        Throws:
        NMSException - If there was any issue while assigning NBT data.

      • fromItemMeta

        Returns:
        an NBT-like representation of the specified item meta.

      • addToItemStack

        public static org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack addToItemStack(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item,
                                                            Map<String,Object> tags)
                                                     throws NMSException
        Replaces the tags in the given ItemStack by the given tags.

        This operation is only possible on a CraftItemStack. As a consequence, this method returns an ItemStack. If the given ItemStack was a CraftItemStack, the same instance will be returned, but in the other cases, it will be a new one (a copy).

        Parameters:
        item - The ItemStack to change.
        tags - The tags to place inside the stack.
        Returns:
        An item stack with the modification applied. It may (if you given a CraftItemStack) or may not (else) be the same instance as the given one.
        Throws:
        NMSException - if the operation cannot be executed.
        See Also:
        This method is equivalent to this one with replace = true.

      • addToItemStack

        public static org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack addToItemStack(org.bukkit.inventory.ItemStack item,
                                                            Map<String,Object> tags,
                                                            boolean replace)
                                                     throws NMSException
        Adds or replaces the tags in the given ItemStack by the given tags.

        This operation is only possible on a CraftItemStack. As a consequence, this method returns an ItemStack. If the given ItemStack was a CraftItemStack, the same instance will be returned, but in the other cases, it will be a new one (a copy).

        Parameters:
        item - The ItemStack to change.
        tags - The tags to place inside the stack.
        replace - true to replace the whole set of tags. If false, tags will be added.
        Returns:
        An item stack with the modification applied. It may (if you given a CraftItemStack) or may not (else) be the same instance as the given one.
        Throws:
        NMSException - if the operation cannot be executed.

      • toNBTJSONString

        public static String toNBTJSONString(Object value)
        Returns the NBT JSON representation of the given object. This method returns a non-strict JSON representation of the object, because minecraft (both client and server) can't deal with strict JSON for some item nbt tags.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to JSONify.
        Returns:
        the NBT JSON representation of the given object.
